#: ../../../style-guide.rst:70
msgid "We have a specific way that we write common words:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:72
msgid ""
"``build command`` is the name of each step in the file. We try to avoid "
"confusion with pipelines, jobs and steps from other CIs, as we do not have a "
"multi-dimentional build sequence."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:75
msgid ""
"``build job`` is the name of the general and pre-defined steps that can be "
"overridden. They are similar to \"steps\" in pipelines, but on Read the Docs "
"they are pre-defined. So it's important to have a unique name."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:79
msgid ""
"``Git`` should be upper case. Except when referring to the :program:`git` "
"command, then it should be written as `:program:\\`git\\``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:80
msgid ""
"``Git repository`` for the place that stores Git repos. We used to use "
"``VCS``, but this is deprecated."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:81
msgid ""
"``Git provider`` for generic references to GitHub/Bitbucket/GitLab/Gitea "
"etc. We avoid \"host\" and \"platform\" because they are slightly more "
"ambiguous."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:83
msgid ""
"``how to`` do the thing is explained in a ``how-to guide`` (notice hyphen "
"and spaces)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:84
msgid "``lifecycle`` is spelled without hyphen nor space."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:85
msgid ""
"``open source`` should be lower case, unless you are definitely referring to "
"`OSI's Open Source Definition <https://opensource.org/osd>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:86
msgid ""
"``.readthedocs.yaml`` is the general name of the build configuration file. "
"Even though we allow custom paths to the config file, we only validate ``."
"readthedocs.yaml`` as the file name. Older variations of the name are "
"considered legacy. We do not refer to it in general terms."
msgstr ""

