#: ../../../style-guide.rst:103
msgid "Glossary"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:105
msgid ""
"Since the above Word List is for internal reference, we also maintain a :doc:"
"`rtd:glossary` with terms that have canonical definitions in our docs. Terms "
"that can otherwise have multiple definitions *or* have a particular meaning "
"in Read the Docs context should always be added to the :doc:`rtd:glossary` "
"and referenced using the ``:term:`` role."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:111
msgid ""
"Using a glossary helps us (authors) to have consistent definitions but even "
"more importantly, it helps and includes readers by giving them quick and "
"easy access to terms that they may be unfamiliar with."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:115
msgid ""
"Use an external link or Intersphinx reference when a term is clearly defined "
"elsewhere."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:118
msgid "Cross-references"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:120
msgid ""
"Cross-references are great to have as :ref:`inline links <style-guide:Cross-"
"references>`. Because of sphinx-hoverxref_, inline links also have a nice "
"tooltip displayed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../style-guide.rst:124
msgid ""
"We like to cross-reference other articles with a definition list inside a "
"``seealso::`` admonition box. It looks like this:"
